{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/xen0l/awesome-dtrace/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c83f8fa1-b939-55ee-a609-2987ab7393b6","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-dtrace-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-dtrace-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome dtrace awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome DTrace <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<p>A curated list of awesome DTrace books, articles, videos, tools and resources.</p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#learn\">Learn</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#articles\">Articles</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#videos\">Videos</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#software\">Software</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#tools\">Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#community\">Community</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#contributing\">Contributing</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"learn\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#learn\" aria-label=\"learn permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Learn</h2>\n<p>Recommended reading for learning DTrace.</p>\n<h3 id=\"books\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#books\" aria-label=\"books permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Books</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/guide/preface.html\">Dynamic Tracing Guide</a> - Illumos.org DTrace guide.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.dtracebook.com/index.php/Main_Page\">DTrace: Dynamic Tracing in Oracle Solaris, Mac OS X, and FreeBSD</a> - Official DTrace book.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://myaut.github.io/dtrace-stap-book/\">Dynamic Tracing with DTrace &#x26; SystemTap</a> - A book introduces both DTrace and SystemTap.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"other\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#other\" aria-label=\"other permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://illumos.org/man/1m/dtrace\">dtrace(1m) man page</a> - DTrace manual page.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.brendangregg.com/DTrace/DTrace-cheatsheet.pdf\">DTrace cheatsheet</a> - DTrace cheatsheet by Brendan Gregg.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.brendangregg.com/DTrace/dtrace_oneliners.txt\">DTrace one-liners</a> - DTrace one liners. Handy commands.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.freebsd.org/DTrace/One-Liners\">DTrace one-liners (FreeBSD)</a> - DTrace one liners from FreeBSD.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.tablespace.net/quicksheet/dtrace-quickstart.html\">DTrace QuickStart</a> - DTrace quick starting guide.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/NanXiao/using-dtrace-stories\">Using DTrace stories</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/NanXiao/using-dtrace-stories\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">20</span></span></a> - A collection of using DTrace to debug system stories.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/resources/bmc/dtrace_tips.pdf\">Advanced DTrace Tips, Tricks and Gotchas</a> - A collection of advanced tips for using DTrace.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"articles\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#articles\" aria-label=\"articles permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Articles</h2>\n<p>Interesting articles about DTrace and real-world use cases.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pid-provider\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pid-provider\" aria-label=\"pid provider permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>PID Provider</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/brendan/2011/02/09/dtrace-pid-provider/\">pid provider: entry probe</a> - DTrace PID Provider.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/brendan/2011/02/11/dtrace-pid-provider-arguments/\">pid provider: entry arguments</a> - DTrace PID Provider Arguments.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/brendan/2011/02/14/dtrace-pid-provider-return/\">pid provider: return</a> - DTrace PID Provider return.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/brendan/2011/02/16/dtrace-pid-provider-instructions/\">pid provider: instructions</a> - DTrace PID Provider Instructions.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/brendan/2011/02/18/dtrace-pid-provider-overhead/\">pid provider: overhead</a> - DTrace PID Provider Overhead.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/ahl/2005/03/01/pid-provider-exposed/\">pid provider exposed</a> - PID providers internals by Adam Leventhal.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/bmc/2011/03/09/when-magic-collides/\">When magic collides</a> - PID provider bug deep dive by Bryan Cantrill.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"usdt-provider\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#usdt-provider\" aria-label=\"usdt provider permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>USDT provider</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/dap/2013/11/20/understanding-dtrace-ustack-helpers/\">Understanding DTrace ustack helpers</a> - DTrace ustack helpers.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dtrace.org/blogs/dap/2011/12/13/usdt-providers-redux/\">USDT Providers Redux</a> - Reference for building USDT providers in custom applications.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"sysevent-provider\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sysevent-provider\" aria-label=\"sysevent provider permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sysevent provider</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blogs.oracle.com/eschrock/entry/dtrace_sysevent_provider\">DTrace sysevent provider</a> - Solaris/illumos sysevent provider for DTrace.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ruby-and-dtrace\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ruby-and-dtrace\" aria-label=\"ruby and dtrace permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Ruby and DTrace</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://vaneyckt.io/posts/using_dtrace_to_measure_mutex_contention_in_ruby/\">Using DTrace to measure mutex contention in Ruby</a> - Mutex contention measuring in Ruby.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"visualization-methods\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#visualization-methods\" aria-label=\"visualization methods permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Visualization methods</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.brendangregg.com/flamegraphs.html\">Flamegraphs</a> - A visualization of profiled software, allowing the most frequent code-paths to be identified quickly and accurately.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://brendangregg.com/heatmaps.html\">Heat Maps</a> - Heat maps allow three dimensions of data to be visualized, similar to weather radar maps where color is used as a dimension.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"videos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#videos\" aria-label=\"videos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Videos</h2>\n<p>Interesting videos about DTrace.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TgmA48fILq8\">DTrace review</a> - Bryan Cantrill explains how to significantly improve debugging both for development and live systems with DTrace.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"dtraceconf\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#dtraceconf\" aria-label=\"dtraceconf permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>dtrace.conf</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/RvyP61WeFdM?list=PL85